comment:
* Contains precise disconnect call causes generated by the framework and the RIL.
 * @hide

variables.name: NOT_VALID
variables.comment: The disconnect cause is not valid (Not received a disconnect cause).

variables.name: NO_DISCONNECT_CAUSE_AVAILABLE
variables.comment: No disconnect cause provided. Generally a local disconnect or an incoming missed call.

variables.name: UNOBTAINABLE_NUMBER
variables.comment:
* The destination cannot be reached because the number, although valid,
     * is not currently assigned.

variables.name: NO_ROUTE_TO_DESTINATION
variables.comment:
* The user cannot be reached because the network through which the call has been routed does
     * not serve the destination desired.

variables.name: CHANNEL_UNACCEPTABLE
variables.comment:
* The channel most recently identified is not acceptable to the sending entity for use in this
     * call.

variables.name: OPERATOR_DETERMINED_BARRING
variables.comment:
* The mobile station (MS) has tried to access a service that the MS's network operator or
     * service provider is not prepared to allow.

variables.name: NORMAL
variables.comment: One of the users involved in the call has requested that the call is cleared.

variables.name: BUSY
variables.comment: The called user is unable to accept another call.

variables.name: NO_USER_RESPONDING
variables.comment:
* The user does not respond to a call establishment message with either an alerting or connect
     * indication within the prescribed period of time allocated.

variables.name: NO_ANSWER_FROM_USER
variables.comment:
* The user has provided an alerting indication but has not provided a connect indication
     * within a prescribed period of time.

variables.name: CALL_REJECTED
variables.comment: The equipment sending this cause does not wish to accept this call.

variables.name: NUMBER_CHANGED
variables.comment: The called number is no longer assigned.

variables.name: PREEMPTION
variables.comment:
* This cause is returned to the network when a mobile station clears an active call which is
     * being pre-empted by another call with higher precedence.

variables.name: DESTINATION_OUT_OF_ORDER
variables.comment:
* The destination indicated by the mobile station cannot be reached because the interface to
     * the destination is not functioning correctly.

variables.name: INVALID_NUMBER_FORMAT
variables.comment: The called party number is not a valid format or is not complete.

variables.name: FACILITY_REJECTED
variables.comment: The facility requested by user can not be provided by the network.

variables.name: STATUS_ENQUIRY
variables.comment: Provided in response to a STATUS ENQUIRY message.

variables.name: NORMAL_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: Reports a normal disconnect only when no other normal cause applies.

variables.name: NO_CIRCUIT_AVAIL
variables.comment: There is no channel presently available to handle the call.

variables.name: NETWORK_OUT_OF_ORDER
variables.comment:
* The network is not functioning correctly and that the condition is likely to last a
     * relatively long period of time.

variables.name: TEMPORARY_FAILURE
variables.comment:
* The network is not functioning correctly and the condition is not likely to last a long
     * period of time.

variables.name: SWITCHING_CONGESTION
variables.comment: The switching equipment is experiencing a period of high traffic.

variables.name: ACCESS_INFORMATION_DISCARDED
variables.comment: The network could not deliver access information to the remote user as requested.

variables.name: CHANNEL_NOT_AVAIL
variables.comment: The channel cannot be provided.

variables.name: RESOURCES_UNAVAILABLE_OR_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment:
* This cause is used to report a resource unavailable event only when no other cause in the
     * resource unavailable class applies.

variables.name: QOS_NOT_AVAIL
variables.comment: The requested quality of service (ITU-T X.213) cannot be provided.

variables.name: REQUESTED_FACILITY_NOT_SUBSCRIBED
variables.comment:
* The facility could not be provided by the network because the user has no complete
     * subscription.

variables.name: INCOMING_CALLS_BARRED_WITHIN_CUG
variables.comment: Incoming calls are not allowed within this calling user group (CUG).

variables.name: BEARER_CAPABILITY_NOT_AUTHORIZED
variables.comment: The mobile station is not authorized to use bearer capability requested.

variables.name: BEARER_NOT_AVAIL
variables.comment: The requested bearer capability is not available at this time.

variables.name: SERVICE_OPTION_NOT_AVAILABLE
variables.comment: The service option is not availble at this time.

variables.name: BEARER_SERVICE_NOT_IMPLEMENTED
variables.comment: The equipment sending this cause does not support the bearer capability requested.

variables.name: ACM_LIMIT_EXCEEDED
variables.comment: The call clearing is due to ACM being greater than or equal to ACMmax.

variables.name: REQUESTED_FACILITY_NOT_IMPLEMENTED
variables.comment: The equipment sending this cause does not support the requested facility.

variables.name: ONLY_DIGITAL_INFORMATION_BEARER_AVAILABLE
variables.comment:
* The equipment sending this cause only supports the restricted version of the requested bearer
     * capability.

variables.name: SERVICE_OR_OPTION_NOT_IMPLEMENTED
variables.comment: The service requested is not implemented at network.

variables.name: INVALID_TRANSACTION_IDENTIFIER
variables.comment:
* The equipment sending this cause has received a message with a transaction identifier
     * which is not currently in use on the mobile station network interface.

variables.name: USER_NOT_MEMBER_OF_CUG
variables.comment:
* The called user for the incoming CUG call is not a member of the specified calling user
     * group (CUG).

variables.name: INCOMPATIBLE_DESTINATION
variables.comment: The equipment sending this cause has received a request which can't be accomodated.

variables.name: SEMANTICALLY_INCORRECT_MESSAGE
variables.comment: This cause is used to report receipt of a message with semantically incorrect contents.

variables.name: INVALID_MANDATORY_INFORMATION
variables.comment:
* The equipment sending this cause has received a message with a non-semantical mandatory
     * information element (IE) error.

variables.name: MESSAGE_TYPE_NON_IMPLEMENTED
variables.comment:
* This is sent in response to a message which is not defined, or defined but not implemented
     * by the equipment sending this cause.

variables.name: MESSAGE_TYPE_NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_PROTOCOL_STATE
variables.comment:
* The equipment sending this cause has received a message not compatible with the protocol
     * state.

variables.name: INFORMATION_ELEMENT_NON_EXISTENT
variables.comment:
* The equipment sending this cause has received a message which includes information
     * elements not recognized because its identifier is not defined or it is defined but not
     * implemented by the equipment sending the cause.

variables.name: CONDITIONAL_IE_ERROR
variables.comment: The equipment sending this cause has received a message with conditional IE errors.

variables.name: MESSAGE_NOT_COMPATIBLE_WITH_PROTOCOL_STATE
variables.comment: The message has been received which is incompatible with the protocol state.

variables.name: RECOVERY_ON_TIMER_EXPIRED
variables.comment:
* The procedure has been initiated by the expiry of a timer in association with
     * 3GPP TS 24.008 error handling procedures.

variables.name: PROTOCOL_ERROR_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment:
* This protocol error event is reported only when no other cause in the protocol error class
     * applies.

variables.name: INTERWORKING_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment:
* Interworking with a network which does not provide causes for actions it takes thus, the
     * precise cause for a message which is being sent cannot be ascertained.

variables.name: CALL_BARRED
variables.comment: The call is restricted.

variables.name: FDN_BLOCKED
variables.comment: The call is blocked by the Fixed Dialing Number list.

variables.name: IMSI_UNKNOWN_IN_VLR
variables.comment: The given IMSI is not known at the Visitor Location Register (VLR) TS 24.008 cause .

variables.name: IMEI_NOT_ACCEPTED
variables.comment:
* The network does not accept emergency call establishment using an IMEI or not accept attach
     * procedure for emergency services using an IMEI.

variables.name: RADIO_OFF
variables.comment: The call cannot be established because RADIO is OFF.

variables.name: OUT_OF_SRV
variables.comment: The call cannot be established because of no cell coverage.

variables.name: NO_VALID_SIM
variables.comment: The call cannot be established because of no valid SIM.

variables.name: RADIO_INTERNAL_ERROR
variables.comment: The call is dropped or failed internally by modem.

variables.name: NETWORK_RESP_TIMEOUT
variables.comment: Call failed because of UE timer expired while waiting for a response from network.

variables.name: NETWORK_REJECT
variables.comment: Call failed because of a network reject.

variables.name: RADIO_ACCESS_FAILURE
variables.comment: Call failed because of radio access failure. ex. RACH failure.

variables.name: RADIO_LINK_FAILURE
variables.comment: Call failed/dropped because of a Radio Link Failure (RLF).

variables.name: RADIO_LINK_LOST
variables.comment: Call failed/dropped because of radio link lost.

variables.name: RADIO_UPLINK_FAILURE
variables.comment: Call failed because of a radio uplink issue.

variables.name: RADIO_SETUP_FAILURE
variables.comment: Call failed because of a RRC (Radio Resource Control) connection setup failure.

variables.name: RADIO_RELEASE_NORMAL
variables.comment: Call failed/dropped because of RRC (Radio Resource Control) connection release from NW.

variables.name: RADIO_RELEASE_ABNORMAL
variables.comment:
* Call failed/dropped because of RRC (Radio Resource Control) abnormally released by
     * modem/network.

variables.name: ACCESS_CLASS_BLOCKED
variables.comment: Call setup failed because of access class barring.

variables.name: NETWORK_DETACH
variables.comment: Call failed/dropped because of a network detach.

variables.name: CDMA_LOCKED_UNTIL_POWER_CYCLE
variables.comment: Mobile station (MS) is locked until next power cycle.

variables.name: CDMA_DROP
variables.comment: Drop call.

variables.name: CDMA_INTERCEPT
variables.comment: INTERCEPT order received, Mobile station (MS) state idle entered.

variables.name: CDMA_REORDER
variables.comment: Mobile station (MS) has been redirected, call is cancelled.

variables.name: CDMA_SO_REJECT
variables.comment: Service option rejection.

variables.name: CDMA_RETRY_ORDER
variables.comment: Requested service is rejected, retry delay is set.

variables.name: CDMA_ACCESS_FAILURE
variables.comment: Unable to obtain access to the CDMA system.

variables.name: CDMA_PREEMPTED
variables.comment: Not a preempted call.

variables.name: CDMA_NOT_EMERGENCY
variables.comment: Not an emergency call.

variables.name: CDMA_ACCESS_BLOCKED
variables.comment: Access Blocked by CDMA network.

variables.name: OEM_CAUSE_1
variables.comment:
OEM specific error codes. To be used by OEMs when they don't want to
       reveal error code which would be replaced by ERROR_UNSPECIFIED

variables.name: ERROR_UNSPECIFIED
variables.comment: Disconnected due to unspecified reasons.
